Faculty Utilization Query Documentation
1. Objective
The query aims to analyze and compare planned vs. conducted faculty lectures across multiple categories and batches. It aggregates data at the faculty × subject × batch × month level, allowing accurate measurement of planned lecture hours and counts (based on internal scheduling system) and conducted lecture hours and counts (based on actual class execution). The final dataset enables analysis of discrepancies between planned and conducted sessions. 
2. Data Sources
The query uses the following tables as primary data sources:
- central.gold_schedule_planner_mappings	: Internal lecture scheduling metadata – Source for planned lectures
- cdp_revenue.gold_batches_pw: Batch master data – Category mapping and batch information
- cdp_revenue.gold_subjects_pw: Subject master data – Subject-level metadata
- cdp_revenue.gold_users_pw: User/faculty master data – Mapping of teacher IDs to faculty names
- mview.gold_dbt_lecture_batch_info: Lecture execution-level metadata – Source for conducted lectures
- user_experience.gold_videos: Recorded video metadata – Source for recorded sessions and durations
3. Query Structure
The query follows a Common Table Expression (CTE) structure with three major layers:
1. planned_agg – Aggregates planned lectures and hours.
2. workload_agg – Aggregates conducted (actual) lectures and hours.
3. final/xoxo – Combines both datasets and applies category leader mapping.
4. Planned CTE (planned_agg)
This CTE aggregates all scheduled (planned) lectures and computes total planned hours and lecture counts per faculty, subject, and batch.
Source Tables & Joins
- central.gold_schedule_planner_mappings: Base table for planned lecture data
- cdp_revenue.gold_batches_pw: Maps batch details and exam categories
- cdp_revenue.gold_subjects_pw: Maps subject names
- cdp_revenue.gold_users_pw: Maps faculty names
Key Columns & Logic
• planned_hours = date_diff('minute', date, enddate) / 60.0 – Calculates total planned lecture hours.
• lecture_month = date_trunc('month', date) – Identifies lecture month for aggregation.
• lecture_count = count(subjectwiselecturenumber) – Number of planned lectures.
• nexam – Normalized exam category derived from financeexamcategory via CASE mapping.
5. Workload CTE (workload_agg)
This CTE aggregates actual conducted lectures and computes total conducted hours and number of lectures delivered per faculty.
- mview.gold_dbt_lecture_batch_info: Base table containing actual lecture execution data
- user_experience.gold_videos: Provides video duration and creation timestamps
Key Columns & Logic
• conducted_hours = sum(video_duration) / 3600.0 – Converts duration from seconds to hours.
• lecture_month = date_trunc('month', conduct_date) – Monthly aggregation.
• lecture_count = count(distinct bss_id) – Total conducted lectures.
• nexam – Normalized exam category derived from new_exam_category via CASE mapping.
6. Final Merge (final)
Performs a full outer join between planned_agg and workload_agg to align planned vs conducted data for each faculty-subject-batch combination.
Join Conditions:

p.nexam = w.nexam AND p.batchid = w.batch_id AND p.subject_name = w.subject AND p.teacherid = w.teacher_id AND p.enddate = w.lecture_time AND p.lecture_month = w.lecture_month.
7. Leadership Mapping (xoxo)
Maps each exam category (nexam) to its corresponding category leader for ownership tracking.
- MANISH: Commerce, CA, MBA, CLAT, IIT JAM, UGC NET, CS, CSIR NET, Nursing Exams, IPMAT, CUET PG, Pharma, Design_Wallah, IELTS, CA Final, ACCA, NEET_PG, CA Offline, MBA_GMAT, BFSI, TOEFL
- PRASHANT: SSC, Banking, WBPSC, TET, JAIIB AND CAIIB, State Exams
- RAJAT: UPSC, BPSC, UPPSC, MPSC, Agriculture, MPPSC, Judiciary, GATE, AE/JE, OPSC
- SANYAM: IIT-JEE, NEET, Foundation, Pre_Foundation, STATE BOARDS, Defence, Vernacular, CUET UG, Bharat Batch, Olympiad
- ANKIT: Power Batch
8. Key Calculations
• Planned Hours = date_diff('minute', date, enddate) / 60.0
• Conducted Hours = sum(video_duration) / 3600.0
• Lecture Month = date_trunc('month', lecture_time)
• Adjusted Hours = planned_hours + 1.0, conducted_hours + 1.0
• Lecture Count = count(distinct lecture IDs)
9. Output Columns
- Leader: Category Leader assigned per nexam
- nexam: Normalized Exam Category
- batchid: Batch Identifier
- subject: Subject Name
- facultyid: Faculty Identifier
- faculty_name: Faculty Name
- lecture_time: Lecture Date (Planned or Conducted)
- lecture_month: Monthly bucket for reporting
- planned_lectures: Total planned lectures count
- conducted_lectures: Total conducted lectures count
- planned_hours: Planned lecture duration (in hours)
- conducted_hours: Conducted lecture duration (in hours)

