Appendix C — FAQs: Filters, Metrics, and Calculations
Note on Utilisation Benchmark: Utilisation % is computed at a monthly grain using a benchmark of 120 hours per faculty per month. For roll-ups spanning multiple faculties and/or months, the utilisation is computed as Total Hours ÷ (120 × #Distinct Faculty-Months).
Q1. What are the filters available for end users to personalize the metrics on the dashboard?
Users can filter data on the following levers: Leader, Exam Category (nexam), Faculty Name, Batch, Month Range, and Week Range.
Q2. What is the total number of planned lectures?
Metric: Planned Lectures (from Planned section).
Calculation: SUM(planned_lectures) over the selected filters.
Q3. How many lectures were actually conducted?
Metric: Conducted Lectures (from Conducted section).
Calculation: SUM(conducted_lectures) over the selected filters.
Q4. What is the total planned lecture duration in hours?
Metric: Planned Hours (from Planned section).
Calculation: SUM(planned_hours) over the selected filters.
Q5. What is the total conducted lecture duration in hours?
Metric: Conducted Hours (from Conducted section).
Calculation: SUM(conducted_hours) over the selected filters.
Q6. What is the overall planned utilisation percentage?
Metric: Utilisation % (Planned).
Calculation (per faculty × month) : planned_hours ÷ 120. 
Roll-up across multiple faculty/months: SUM(planned_hours) ÷ (120 × COUNT_DISTINCT(facultyid, lecture_month)).
Q7. What is the overall conducted utilisation percentage?
Metric: Utilisation % (Conducted).
Calculation (per faculty × month): conducted_hours ÷ 120. 
Roll-up across multiple faculty/months: SUM(conducted_hours) ÷ (120 × COUNT_DISTINCT(facultyid, lecture_month)).
Additional Note — Week Range Filters
The utilisation percentage is defined on a monthly benchmark (120 hours). When Week Range is used, hours may be displayed by week for exploration, but utilisation % is still computed against the monthly benchmark by aggregating weeks into their corresponding months within the selected range.
Appendix C — Q7 Addendum: Multi‑Month Utilisation Calculation
Scope & Benchmark: 
Utilisation % (Conducted) is benchmarked at 120 hours per faculty per month. When the selected period spans multiple months, the denominator scales with the month count.
Single Faculty over N Months
Formula:  Utilisation % = SUM(conducted_hours) ÷ (120 × N_months)
Example (2 months):  If a faculty conducted 150 hours across the two months → 150 ÷ (120 × 2) = 62.5%.
Multiple Faculties over Multiple Months
Preferred formula (per‑faculty capacity):  Utilisation % = SUM(conducted_hours) ÷ (120 × COUNT_DISTINCT(facultyid, lecture_month))
This treats each faculty‑month as 120 hours of capacity. For example, with 2 faculties over 2 months each (4 faculty‑months total), the denominator is 120 × 4 = 480.

